// Codex audit P2-16: the legacy `str` type was a transitional
// alias for the canonical `String` stdlib struct during the
// strâ†’String rewrite. CLAUDE.md and the design docs say
// there is no `str â†’ String` sugar, but the parser silently
// accepted `str` in type positions and treated it as `String`.
//
// Now `str` in any type position errors at the parser with a
// teaching message: use `String` from `std/string`.

greet(x str) {
  yell(x)
}

spark {
  greet("hello")
}
